<DATE_TIME> 1999-11-30 19:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gaddafi Calls for Intensifying African Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TRIPOLI, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi
Tuesday urged unity among African countries, saying this is the
precondition for national progress and economic development, and a
powerful weapon to halt conflicts on the continent.
</P>
<P>
Gaddafi made the remarks at a big gathering in Tripoli to
celebrate Patriotic Movement of Salvation, led by Chadian
President Idriss Deby, being in power for nine years.
</P>
<P>
Gaddafi said any conflicts on the African continent is the
treason to the African unity for they can only cause more
sufferings for the African people and are to the advantage of
African countries' enemies.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he called on the African countries to adopt positive
approaches to solve their disputes so as to achieve security and
stability on the African continent.
</P>
<P>
On the relations with Chad, Gaddafi said this is first time for
a country to mark its national day on the Libyan territory, which
ultimately manifest the unity between Libya and Chad.
</P>
<P>
Gaddafi also criticized the intervention by the U.S.-led West in
the internal affairs of Africa, saying the African people can
safeguard their independence and democracy and they categorically
reject external interference and hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Chad President Deby expressed thanks to Gaddafi
for his support and help for the Chadian people in their fights
against invasion and efforts to develop national economy,
especially in oil tapping.
</P>
<P>
Deby and his party arrived here earlier in the day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
