<HEADLINE> Syrian President Meets British Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez
Al-Assad met with British envoy Michael Levy Tuesday on the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Levy, British Prime Minister Tony Blair's personal envoy,
conveyed to Assad a message from Blair, the Arab Syrian News
Agency (ASNA) reported. But it did not give the content of the
message.
</P>
<P>
Levy expressed Britain's interest in the peace process in
general and the Syrian and Lebanese tracks of talks with Israel in
particular.
</P>
<P>
The peace talks on Palestinian-Israeli track have entered the
final stage, with the two sides vowing to hammer out a framework
agreement next February and a permanent peace deal next September.
</P>
<P>
Israel and Syria are contacting on the resumption of their
stalled talks, but no tangible progress has been made.
</P>
<P>
Assad and Levy also dealt with the bilateral ties and ways of
developing cooperation in various fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
