<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Defense Minister Says Kosovo Serbs Face Ethnic Cleansing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 30 (Xinhua) -- French Defense Minister Alain
Richard said on Tuesday that France prefers to see a division of
Kosovo rather than an elimination of the Serb community there
faced with ``another ethnic cleansing.''
</P>
<P>
At a conference on Central European security hosted by the
Institute of High Studies of National Defense, Richard said that
France prefers a re-grouping of the Serbs into certain areas of
Kosovo to protect them from the Kosovo Albanians.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks when answering a question posed by former
Albanian Defense Minister Alfred Moisiu on what he thought about
the risks a division of Kosovo could bring about.
</P>
<P>
Richard said that ``another ethnic cleansing'' is taking place
in Kosovo, this time against the Serbs.
</P>
<P>
``Our choice has been between the risk of a division of Kosovo
because the frightened Serb population are regrouped in a certain
number of areas to avoid the massacres, and the elimination by
terror of the Serb community,'' he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
