<HEADLINE> Angolan Rebels Launch Attacks in Central Highland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Angolan rebels have launched a
new round of raids on the government targets, attacking the town
of Wago Kungo and ambushing tanker trucks belonging to the state
oil company Sonangol.
</P>
<P>
According to official source, Angolan government forces and the
rebels of the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) are currently engaged in "violent combats" around the town
of Waco Kungo.
</P>
<P>
The heavy fighting, which began early Monday, was taking place
around the airport, located some 10 km from the town center.
Telephone communications with Sumbe, capital of South Kwanza
Province, remained down Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
No further details of the fighting were immediately available.
</P>
<P>
Last weekend, three tanker trucks of the state oil company
Sonangol were destroyed by presumed UNITA rebels in central
Angola's Huambo Province, according to a police source.
</P>
<P>
The trucks, which were transporting fuel from the southern
city of Lubango, were ambushed by gunmen south of Caala. 
</P>
</TEXT>
