<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Confirms Plan to Visit West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
on Tuesday confirmed to visiting Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat that he plans to visit the West Bank early next year.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin is being treated at the Central Clinical Hospital for
suspected pneumonia. He said in a telephone conversation with
Arafat that he would visit the city of Bethlehem in early January
as part of Orthodox celebrations to mark the 2000th anniversary of
Christ's birth.
</P>
<P>
"The president confirmed that he would visit holy sites in
Palestine as earlier planned," the Interfax news agency quoted
Arafat as saying at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin reiterated Moscow's support for the Palestinians' right
to self-determination and the creation of their own state, Kremlin
spokesman Dmitry Yakushkin said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who arrived here Monday on a two-day working visit, has
left Moscow Tuesday for Cairo, Egypt. He also held meetings with
Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin and Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov during the visit. 
</P>
