<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Grants Assistance for Education in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 30 (Xinhua) -- The European Union has
agreed to provide about 20 million U.S. dollars in grant
assistance for the implementation of a basic and primary education
program in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
The program, which is being implemented over a period of five
years beginning the fiscal year 1999/2000, aims to enhance the
enrollment of primary schools, improving learning achievement, and
building institutional capacity in planning, monitoring and
improving the performance of primary level of education.
</P>
<P>
The program is expected to benefit about 3.3 million children
in government-aided schools and 300,000 children in alternative
schools.
</P>
<P>
Upon the completion of the program in 2004, net enrollment
ratio and primary cycle completion ratio are expected to reach 90
percent and 75 percent from the present levels of 79 percent and
41 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The program is financed by a consortium of donors, including
the World Bank, Denmark, Finland, Norway and the European Union.
Other donors providing support to the sub-sectors include Japan,
the Asian Development Bank and the United Nations Children's Fund.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
