<HEADLINE> Schroeder Expects European Defense Concretized in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 30 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder expected on Tuesday that an autonomous defense capacity
of European Union (EU) countries will be concretized during France
's rotating EU presidency in the second half of 2000.
</P>
<P>
In a speech addressed to the French National Assembly,
Schroeder said that the decisions concerning the definition of the
policy of security and defense of EU would be adopted under the
French presidency, so that EU could have an increased capacity of
military action.
</P>
<P>
"That will be an important step in which we will fully support
France," said the chancellor, who was here to attend the 74th
Franco-German summit.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder and French President Jacques Chirac announced on
Tuesday that France, Germany, Britain and Italy have agreed upon a
plan on military structures for the future European defense force
within the EU.
</P>
<P>
"In concertation with our British friends, Germany and France
will make sure that these efforts be achieved under the French
presidency,'' said Schroeder.
</P>
<P>
The Franco-German declaration followed the one made by France
and Britain last Thursday in London, which calls for the
establishment of an autonomous European force of from 50,000 to 60,
000 men, who are capable of dealing with crises without
participation of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Such a European force is aimed at reinforcing the ``European
pillar'' of NATO, said officials in Paris, Berlin and London.
</P>
</TEXT>
