<HEADLINE> Italy Urges to Help Avert Russia's Isolation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In reporting on the situation in the Caucusus, Ranieri said
Chechyna at present poses the chief danger to relations between
the Kremlin and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
"An isolated Russia constitutes a much greater threat than a
Russia aware of its role as a continental power ready to shoulder
the obligations that derive from international cooperation," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Russia's passage from a military to a regional policy in
Chechnya is "inevitable", he claimed.
</P>
<P>
Europe must follow this tack, in keeping with the approach
adopted in Istanbul earlier this month by the 54-nation
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE).
</P>
<P>
