<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Sweden Initial Debt Rescheduling Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Tuesday initialed
an agreement with Sweden for rescheduling a 93 million U.S. dollar
debt as part of an overall relief package of 3.3 billion dollars
arranged by the Paris Club creditors, government sources said.
</P>
<P>
With the signing of the accord with Sweden, Pakistan has
already concluded agreements with nine countries, involving the
debt relief of around 1.4 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth accord of its kind in a week. Pakistan has
signed debt rescheduling agreements with the United States,
Germany and Norway.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, Pakistan signed a 926 million dollar debt
rescheduling accord with the United States, followed by similar
agreements with Germany and Norway for the amounts of 255 million
dollars and 11.63 million dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has already signed bilateral agreements for debt
rescheduling with Denmark, Austria and Spain. Under these
agreements, Pakistan has obtained debt relief of 22 million
dollars from Austria, 23 million dollars from Spain and 4 million
dollars from Denmark.
</P>
<P>
According to sources at the Finance Ministry, agreements with
Canada and the Netherlands have also been initialed. Formal
signing will take place soon after clearance by the respective
governments.
</P>
<P>
The agreement with Sweden was initialed here following a day of
negotiations between the Pakistani government and the visiting
Swedish delegation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will be formally signed later as soon as it is
cleared by the government of Sweden, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
