<HEADLINE> Vietnamese President to Visit Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese President Tran Duc
Luong will pay an official visit to Algeria from December 5-7 at
the invitation of Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika,
according to a communique of the Vietnamese Foreign Ministry on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the two countries' leaders are expected to
discuss cooperation in the fields of construction, oil and gas,
and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Algeria established diplomatic relations in October
1962.
</P>
<P>
Luong's visit is aimed at further strengthening its traditional
relations with Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will consider sending Vietnamese agricultural
specialists to Algeria, while Algeria plans to use part of
Vietnam's debts to it, which total 150 million U.S. dollars, to
re-invest in tea and coffee growing and processing in Vietnam for
export to Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Algeria have signed a number of cooperation
agreements in trade, economy, science and technology, culture and
information, an agreement on visa exemption for diplomatic and
business passport bearers, and another on investment promotion and
protection.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministries of the two countries have also signed a
cooperation protocol. 
</P>
</TEXT>
