<HEADLINE> Russia Condemns U.S.-British Bombing of Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Tuesday condemned the
United States and Britain for their bombing of Iraq civilian sites
last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The continued bombing represents "a glaring violation of the
fundamental norms and principles of international law and morality,
" the ministry said in a report carried by the Interfax news
agency.
</P>
<P>
On November 28, Anglo-American aircraft attacked civilian
targets near the Iraqi town of Mosul, wounding eight peaceful
civilians, including women and children, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It said claims by Washington and London that "their actions are
legitimate... hold no water" because the so-called no-fly zones
have been arbitrarily set without U.N. Security Council approval.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry also regards as inconsistent suggestions
that the strikes are in "self-defense."
</P>
<P>
What this amounts to, the report said, is "the arbitrarily
assumed right to patrol the air space of a sovereign country."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
