<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, November 30 (Xinhua) -- The Bolivian government said
Tuesday that it will reject any request for political asylum from
Paraguay's former coup leader General Lino Oviedo.
</P>
<P>
Peru's Information Minister Jorge Landivar told the press that
their main interest is "to keep on good terms with Paraguay."
</P>
<P>
According to reports, Oviedo's lawyers have initiated contact
with the Bolivian authorities with a view to possible political
asylum for Oviedo in Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Argentina and Paraguay became tense after
Argentina's refusal to extradite Oviedo to Paraguay on September 2.
Oviedo has resided in Argentina since his self-exile on March 28.
</P>
<P>
The Bolivian minister said, "It is probable, without stating
specific reasons, that an application for asylum from Oviedo will
be refused."
</P>
<P>
Oviedo's supporters believe his asylum status in Argentina may
be disrupted on December 10 after the entry of the new president-
elect, Fernando de la Rua.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay is accusing Oviedo of being one of the intellectual
authors in the murder of the former vice-president, Jose Maria
Argana, which was carried out on March 13, in Ascuncion. 
</P>
