<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 30 (Xinhua) -- After Prime Minister Ehud
Barak met with Likud party's leader Ariel Sharon Tuesday night,
rumors spread fast that the major right-wing opposition party may
be invited to join the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Barak briefed Sharon on the latest
developments in the peace talks with the Palestinians, his recent
visits to the U.S. and Britain, and the potential terror attacks
against Jewish interests abroad, Israel Radio reported.
