Judaism has quit the coalition in September. Another
ultra-Orthodox Shas party, which controls 17 seats, also has
threatened to quit to protest against the government's accusation
of its educational network.
</P>
<P>
In order to reach a framework agreement in final-status
negotiations with the Palestinians by next February and final
peace treaty by September 2000, Barak needs a more solid and
broad base in the cabinet to support his peace efforts.  
</P>
