<HEADLINE> Canadian Economy Grows in Third Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, November 30 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian economy grew by 1.
2 percent in the July-September quarter over the previous quarter,
Statistics Canada (StatsCan) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It also represents a growth of 3.6 percent in the real gross
domestic product over a year ago, said StatsCan.
</P>
<P>
Despite a moderate increase of 0.2 percent for September, the
economy continued its growth for the 14th consecutive month,
according to the agency.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, StatsCan reported a surplus for the first time since
late 1996 on transactions with foreign countries in terms of goods,
services, investment income and transfers.
</P>
<P>
The surplus was registered at 700 million Canadian dollars (
about 477 million U.S. dollars) in the third quarter, compared
with a deficit of 1.8 billion Canadian dollars (about 1.2 billion
U.S. dollars for the previous quarter. 
</P>
