<HEADLINE> China Imports More Engineering Plastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- China has become the world's
largest engineering plastics importer as its automobile and
telecommunication industries consume a growing amount of
engineering plastics.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the country has imported some 1.5 million tons
of engineering plastics annually over the past four years. The
figure is expected to increase to 1.8 million tons next year,
according to sources from the First China International Exhibition
on Engineering Plastics which opened in Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
Engineering plastics are high technology chemical materials
widely used in industry, agriculture, national defense and in the
daily lives of the Chinese people. The plastics play an
increasingly important role in the manufacture of automobiles,
electronics, construction, and post and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Yang Weicai, chairman of the China Engineering Plastics
Industry Association, said that China's current domestic
production cannot meet the growing demand for the material.
</P>
<P>
The five-day exhibition aims to promote technology and trading
of equipment and related products. The latest engineering plastics
technologies, processing equipment are on display as well as
analysis and testing apparatus from home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Chemicals giants such as Du Pont and BASF are attending the
Exhibition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
