<HEADLINE> Ericsson Helps Southwest China Province to Expand GSM Net </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Ericsson recently signed an
agreement with southwest China's Sichuan Province to provide
equipment and software for Sichuan to expand its GSM net.
</P>
<P>
With total volume of nearly 100 million US dollars, the
contract between the Nanjing Ericsson Telecommunication Co. Ltd
and the Sichuan Mobile Telecommunication Company will help the
province expand its net users from 600,000 to 1.4 million.
</P>
<P>
Besides system equipment, Ericsson will also provide solutions
and technical support for improving net operations. The two
parties will also set up a Maintenance Center in the capital of
the province, Chengdu city, to provide related services.
</P>
<P>
It is the fourth contract that Ericsson has signed in the
province. Ericsson has set up 23 offices and eight joint ventures
in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
