<HEADLINE> Motor Accidents Kill 4,000 Ugandans in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 4,000 Ugandans have been
killed and 744 others injured in motor accidents in the first half
of this year, according to the latest report released by the
Ugandan Police Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The report predicted that the number of victims is expected to
more than double by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Police Officer in Charge of Traffic, Grace Turyagumanawe, said
in the report that a total of 5,048 accidents were recorded
between January and June this year, out of which 644 were fatal
and 1,626 serious.
</P>
<P>
Between 1995 to 1998, a grand total of 37,426 accidents
occurred in the east African country, of which 13.8 percent
involved death and 28 percent serious injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
