<HEADLINE> EU Ranks First Among Albania's Trade Partners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, November 30 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) came
out first among Albania's trade partners during the first nine
months of 1999, as export and import volumes between the two sides
topped 93 and 80 percent respectively out of the total of Albania'
s.
</P>
<P>
Albania's exports to EU countries during the period reached 191.
5 million U.S. dollars, keeping a rising tendency since 1991.
</P>
<P>
In 1991, its exports to the EU took only 39.4 percent while in
1998 the figure reached 92.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The same tendency is also seen in the import sectors. In the
first nine months, Albania's import from the EU topped 710 million
dollars, or 80 percent of the total, while it was 44.2 percent in
1991 and 82.6 percent in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
