<HEADLINE> East China Province Aids Three Gorges Resettlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province,
one of the country's economic powerhouses, has stepped up efforts
to assist the resettlement of local people affected by the Three
Gorges hydro-electric power project on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, the province has invested 55 million yuan (about 6.
6 million U.S. dollars) in 52 businesses in the Three Gorges area,
which have provided thousands of jobs to local people.
</P>
<P>
One of the businesses, the Three Gorges Shoe Co., Ltd., funded
by the Senda Group of Jiangsu, went into operation in April and
now employs 500 local residents.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province has established numerous public
facilities in the area, including 50 schools and a library.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges hydro-electric power project, located near
Yichang in central China's Hubei Province, will cost an estimated
50.09 billion yuan. It will have 26 generating units with a
combined capacity of 18.2 million kw and an annual output of 84.7
billion kwh.
</P>
<P>
The resettlement of more than one million people living in the
dam area started in October of 1992. The entire project is
scheduled for completion in the year 2009.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
