<HEADLINE> Ecological Research Center in Three Gorges Dam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- An ecological research center
was recently established in Chongqing, southwest China, to
strengthen the environmental protection of the Three Gorges Dam
area.
</P>
<P>
The center was jointly set up by six Chongqing-based
institutions including Chongqing University and Chongqing
Environmental Science Research Institute.
</P>
<P>
It has six experimental labs which will monitor the ecological
conditions in the dam area, map out plans to combat water
pollution and study the relations between the environment and
health.
</P>
<P>
Curbing water pollution in the area won't be easy after the
Three Gorges Dam project is completed.
</P>
<P>
Work on the project, the largest of its kind in the world, is
now in full swing. The project involves the damming of the Yangtze
River to create a 1,000 sq km reservoir, over 80 percent of which
is located in the city of Chongqing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
