<HEADLINE> China to Launch Program to Solve Traffic Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Public
Security is to launch a nationwide program next year to solve
urban traffic problems.
</P>
<P>
Meng Hongwei, Director of Traffic Control Bureau Attached to
the Ministry of Public Security, said at a national traffic police
meeting here Tuesday that the program will be launched in over 100
Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
