<HEADLINE> Rockets Olajuwon to Undergo Surgery, out 4-6 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Houston Rockets star center
Hakeem Olajuwon does not have a groin strain. He has a hernia that
requires surgery.
</P>
<P>
Further examinations today revealed an inguinal hernia, which
will sideline Olajuwon for four to six weeks. He initially was
expected to miss three to four weeks with the groin strain.
</P>
<P>
A Rockets spokesman said Olajuwon will have surgery Wednesday
to be performed by team physician.
</P>
<P>
Olajuwon suffered the injury early Friday at Portland and was
sent back to Houston for further examination. He underwent an MRI
Monday that initially revealed no tear but confirmed the strain.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets (4-11) are halfway through a four-game road trip
and visit Phoenix Wednesday. They moved one-half game ahead of
last-placed Vancouver in the Midwest Division after beating the
Grizzlies Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
