<HEADLINE> Curfew Declared in Downtown Seattle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Locke, governor of U.S. Washington state agreed to send in
the National Guard as a response to a request by Seattle Mayor
Paul Schell earlier Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The move came after the day-long protests marked by repeated
clashes between protesters and police, in which police fired tear
gas, pepper spray and rubble pellets at protesters.
</P>
<P>
The third round of WTO talks opened Tuesday with
representatives from 135 nations or areas. 
</P>
