<HEADLINE> Kuchma Sworn in As Ukraine's President for Second Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's President Leonid Kuchma
was sworn in on Tuesday for his second five-year term as the
country's head of state.
</P>
<P>
At a red-carpet inauguration ceremony, Kuchma stressed that his
most important and fundamental task is to improve the people's
livelihood.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma called for economic reform to promote economic growth
and vowed to pursue a foreign policy aimed at developing ties with
both Russia and the United States. He pledged to start radical
reforms of the government.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma also promised to intensify fight against crime and
corruption.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ukrainian constitution, Prime Minister Valery
Pustovoitenko tendered his resignation to Kuchma after the
inauguration ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
