<DOCNO> XIE19991201.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Foundation of Aristocrat's Dwelling Uncovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 1 (Xinhua)-- A large foundation of a dwelling
believed to have been inhabited by aristocrats in the Western Zhou
Dynasty (1100 B.C.-771 B.C.) was discovered recently at the
Zhouyuan Site here, which has been confirmed as the birthplace of
the ancient Zhou people.
</P>
<P>
Covering an area of nearly 300 square meters, the foundation is
21 meters long and 15 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
It has eight one-meter-wide stone bases on which are piled
several layers of blue stones.
</P>
<P>
Two paths lead out from the front of the main entrance, each
two meters wide, which especially caught the attention of
archeologists. The paths are paved with cobblestones that form
flower designs -- a rare sight in Zhou Dynasty archaeological
finds, they said.
</P>
<P>
The experts believed that the construction scale and design of
the foundation suggest aristocrats lived in the house in the Zhou
Dynasty.  
