<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Banks Losses 130 Million Dollars This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's banks have lost 130
million U.S. dollars so far this year, due to the grave economic
situation, said the Banking Superintendents Office Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The losses in the banking sector between January and November
rose over 170 percent, compared with 48 million dollars of the
same period in 1998, said a statement from the office here.
</P>
<P>
The statement attributed the result mainly to the rise of
terminated portfolios, caused by the incapacity of payment of the
productive apparatus.
</P>
<P>
Among the 33 banks at present operating in the country, 10
registered losses and most of the remainders, which have made
profit, are controlled by the Agency of Deposit Guarantee (AGD) of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Mario Canessa, the President of the Association of Private
Banks, said that the increase of the inflation rate and the high
cost of the dollar on the exchange market have affected the banks
and the financial sector negatively. 
</P>
