funded companies in China, according to a national survey
conducted earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
"The HSBC will move its headquarters to Shanghai before long,"
said Wong, who looks upon Shanghai as his hometown.
</P>
<P>
Wong also spoke of China's great achievements and said he
believes the country will hold a significant position in the world
economic system in the coming era.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, jointly organized by the HSBC and Shanghai Fudan
University, will hold four more seminars in the next two years,
and many of the world's economists and other financial experts
will be invited to attend and lecture on economic theory and
practice.
</P>
