<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AIDS Cases Increase in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, November 30 (Xinhua) -- The number of AIDS cases
in Argentina reached over 15,000 in June this year, while that of
HIV positives rose to 110,000, according to the latest bulletin "
AIDS in Argentina".
</P>
<P>
The bulletin released on Tuesday by the Health Ministry also
warned that Aids cases may increase to 17,000 due to the lack of
timely awareness.
</P>
<P>
Describing these figures as "worrying", the experts said the
number of people taking AIDS tests this year has increased to 40
or 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
The experts urged the government to enhance the fight against
the disease, saying that it should be a state policy to carry out
proper prevention programs.
</P>
<P>
Worldwide AIDS epidemic has caused the deaths of 16 million
people since its discovery in 1980, while a reported 33 million
are HIV positives, according to the statistics of the United
Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
