Electronic and Telecommunications Industry of Mexico (CANIETI),
said that at present there are about 250 million computers
worldwide, and the figure may rise to 600 million in 2003.
</P>
<P>
The increase can be attributed mainly to financial loans and
attraction of the Internet, said Valtierra in Guadalajara, capital
of the Mexican state of Jalisco.
</P>
<P>
The businessman pointed out that there will be further growth
in telecommunications next year, especially in equipment related
to the Internet.
</P>
<P>
He also predicted that Internet-related products would increase
five folds compared to computer sales in the next few years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
