<HEADLINE> Woods Named PGA Tour Player of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Tiger Woods of the United
States was named the PGA Tour Player of the Year on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Woods won eight official US PGA Tour events and earned over 6
million dollars prize money in the season.
</P>
<P>
It was the second Player of the Year Trophy for Woods, who also
won in 1997. Woods won seven of his last 10 tournaments and
became the first golfer to win eight events in a season since
Johnny Miller in 1974.
</P>
<P>
"It's a tremendous honor to win this award." said Woods.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Franco of Paraguay, who won the Compaq Classic in New
Orleans and the Greater Milwaukee Open, was named PGA Tour Rookie
of the Year.
</P>
<P>
Steve Pate, whose career was interrupted by two serious
accidents in 1996, was named Comeback Player of the Year. 
</P>
