<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy to Mark AIDS Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Some 30,000 condoms will be
handed out free in Milan Wednesday as one of the initiatives
thought up by Italian authorities to mark World Aids Day.
</P>
<P>
All over the country there will be concerts, publicity events,
public information slots on the radio and a general mobilization
of volunteer groups working with Aids victims and against the
spread of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Some 44,000 cases of Aids have been recorded in Italy since the
start of the epidemic. In the world as a whole some 50 million
people have contracted the HIV virus and 16 million have died.
</P>
<P>
The initiatives planned for Wednesday, as well as encouraging
prevention through the use of condoms, will revolve around the
invitation not to isolate Aids-sufferers but to allow them to
continue a normal life.
</P>
<P>
Campaigners, wearing the customary red ribbon in the button
holes, were already out Tuesday in many cities, including southern
city of Palermo, where hundreds of people gathered for a meeting
attended by Italian Health Minister Rosy Bindi.
</P>
<P>
Part of Bindi's address touched on the new anti-Aids vaccine
developed by Italian researchers.
</P>
<P>
Testing has already begun on five healthy Italians, and the
final stage, which will provide definitive answers concerning the
vaccine's effectiveness, will take place in Uganda, which has one
of the highest levels of Aids cases in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991201.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Launches AIDS Prevention Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZILIA, November 32 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian Health Ministry
on Tuesday announced a national campaign for the prevention of
Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS).
</P>
<P>
With the slogans "Prevention is the beginning of dialogue" and
"Speak live and learn with AIDS", the campaign is aimed at the
youths and adolescents of the country, stimulating parents and
their children to talk about the disease, and will be launched on
December 10.
</P>
<P>
According to the Health Ministry, the more the family speaks
openly about the disease, the more children will understand the
forms of prevention against AIDS.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the distribution of 250,000 posters, the
campaign will also show two films on national television, one
aimed at boys and the other girls.
</P>
<P>
According to information from the Health Ministry, the number
of people infected has remained stable over the last three years
in Brazil, where there are half a million carriers of the Human
Immune Deficiency Virus (HIV), and 163,000 cases of full blown
AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The figures show that while there has been a drop in the number
of male heterosexual and homosexual cases in the country, the
disease is increasing among women of the lower class.
</P>
<P>
On the world-wide list of countries with the highest incident
rate, Brazil is placed 46th, using the incident rate of people
affected per 100,000 inhabitants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
