<HEADLINE> Chief of Paris Olympic Bid Quits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Chief of Paris Olympic Bid
Philippe Bourguignon quit here on Tuesday on the day the city
launched its official campaign for the 2008 summer Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Bourguignon, president of Club Med chosen for his role as a
captain of industry and ability to drum up sponsorship, has stood
down as a result of burgeoning business commitments.
</P>
<P>
"The enormous development of Club Med was becoming incompatible
with the heavy work load generated by the executive commission,"
according to a spokesman for Paris mayor Jean Tiberi.
</P>
<P>
Bourguignon's successor is due to be announced shortly.
</P>
</TEXT>
