early December, Ethiopia News Agency (ENA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In addition, some 152,000 people would also be vaccinated
against measles and diptheria respectively, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Health Ministry announced early this month that
two rounds of nationwide campaign against polio and measles were
to be conducted before the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
About 11 million children are targeted during the 1999 polio
immunization campaign, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
