<HEADLINE> Zambia, Tanzania Sign Transport Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 30 (Xinhua) -- Zambia and Tanzania signed a
road transport agreement here Tuesday to promote, facilitate and
regulate road services between the two countries and in transit to
third party countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is also aimed at ensuring fair competition
between transporters of both the two countries in the carriage of
goods and passengers, a news release said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will simplify the existing administration
requirement in the interest of road transportation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, a joint committee and a joint route
management group will be set up to oversee the implementation of
the agreement.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Zambian Communications and Transport
Minister Nkandu Luo urged the officials from the two countries to
quickly meet so that the implementation can commence as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
"Transporters from the two countries have been making
representations about lack of harmonization which has resulted in
discrimination in some cases. There is therefore urgent need to
remove these disparities," she said.
</P>
<P>
The importance of harmonized regional road transport in
fostering trade and economic development in the region cannot
overstated, the Zambian minister said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian Communications and Transport Minister Ernest Nyanda
said the success in expanding trade and economic relations between
the two countries has to be speared by efficient transport.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the economic and commercial
relations between the two countries will be strengthened in the
spirit of regional cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
