<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HO CHI MINH CITY, Vietnam, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese
Premier Zhu Rongji arrived here Wednesday for a four-day official
visit to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Hanoi, he will meet General Secretary of the
Communist Party of Vietnam Central Committee Le Kha Phieu, Prime
Minister Phan Van Khai and Chairman of the National Assembly Nong
Duc Manh.
</P>
<P>
In Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam's largest city and an important
economic and trade center, Zhu will visit Binh Tien Footwear
Limited Company and Linh Trung Export-Processing Zone.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted by Vietnamese Deputy Foreign Minister Vu Khuan
and Chairman of Ho Chi Minh City People's Committee Vo Viet Thanh
upon his arrival at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Zhu's entourage includes his wife Lao An, Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan, Agriculture Minister Chen Yaobang and Special Assistant
Liu Huaqiu.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is the last leg of Zhu's four-nation visit to Southeast
Asia which has brought him to Malaysia, the Philippines and
Singapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
