<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Kuala Lumpur Stock
Exchange closed mixed Wednesday as investors continued to stay on
the sidelines.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 1.79
points to 732.87, the all-share Emas Index shed 1.18 points to
187.01, the Industrial Index rose 3.58 points to 1,280.18 and the
Second Board fell 1.24 points to 153.10.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 389 to 113 while 145 counters were
unchanged and 270 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover declined to 110.214 million shares
valued at 366.898 million ringgit (about 96.552 million U.S.
dollars) from 177.116 million shares valued at 519.696 million
ringgit (about 136.762 million dollars) on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
