<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Australian stock market
finished lower on Wednesday despite a minor rally just before the
close.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index ended 6.3 points weaker at
3,037.7.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index finished 21.2 points lower at
5,272.9, while the all resources gained 10.4 points to 1,280.7.
</P>
<P>
All the major banks posted rises except ANZ, which suffered a
9.5 cent loss to 11.215 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank added 7.7 cents to 22.777 Australian
dollars, Commonwealth Bank firmed six cents to 26.00 Australian
dollars and Westpac gained 17.5 cents to 10.76 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 703.58 million shares traded for 1.33
billion Australian dollars (878 million U.S. dollars). Falls beat
rises 713 to 621 with 499 stocks steady. 
</P>
