<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 10:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran for Friendship with All Countries: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami said on Wednesday that Iran has stretched out its hands in
friendship and brotherhood towards all the countries of the world,
especially those belonging to the Islamic world.
</P>
<P>
That is the reason why Iran has proposed the theory of "dialog
among civilizations," which has been welcomed by the world
community, Khatami said at the inaugural session of the 5th
Conference of Islamic Information Ministers.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations has named the year 2001 as "the year of
dialog among civilizations" based upon Khatami's proposition, made
soon after he assumed power in August 1997.
</P>
<P>
The moderate president has been pushing forward a policy of
detente in foreign affairs to break Iran's isolation, and
advocating dialog in order to ease tension and reduce mistrust
with world countries, especially its Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
In carrying out the dialog, Khatami said, Islamic countries
enjoy a lofty position, and communication systems constitute the
main instrument for the dialog.
</P>
<P>
Underlining the importance of information, Khatami said that
information and knowledge are one of the principal foundations of
power and prestige.
</P>
<P>
"As we stand at the threshold of the third millennium, we have
no choice but to incorporate these very notions into the inventory
of our current needs and requirements," he said, quoted by the
official Islamic Republic News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Khatami noted that the instruments and mechanism to materialize
the dialog among civilizations will be a balanced system of mass
media, long-distance communication systems and a computer network,
which will bring about desired mutual understanding, development
of rational criticism, and a much greater power of choice in the
societies.
</P>
<P>
Information ministers and deputy minister from 50 Islamic
countries as well as Secretary General of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference (OIC) Ezzidine Laraki attend the two-day
conference of Islamic Information Ministers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
