<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian said here today that China values its relationship with
Greece and he hopes that the two countries will further promote
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
state councilor, made the remarks while meeting with Vice Admiral
Christos Kazassis, Deputy Chief of Hellenic National Defence
General Staff.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that in recent years China and Greece have witnessed
sustained development, and exchanges between their respective
armed forces have helped to improve mutual understanding, trust
and friendship.
</P>
<P>
Chi thanked Greece's support for China in the international
arena. Kazassis said that he is impressed with the high quality of
the Chinese armed forces and hopes to further expand friendly
cooperation with China's military. 
</P>
