<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Sea Fishing Ban Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Ministry of Agriculture
statistics show that a fishing ban on the South China Sea from
June to July has brought sound economic and ecological results.
</P>
<P>
In August and September, fishing output in the area increased
28 percent over the same period last year to 766,000 tons while
shrimp output increased more than 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
A Ministry of Agriculture official said that as a result of the
ban, fish in the South China Sea have grown bigger than before
with an increase number of varieties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
