<HEADLINE> Italy Wins over Spain in World Cup Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Three-time world champions Italy
were made to dig deep into themselves by wild card entrants Spain
for a five-set victory in the World Cup men's volleyball
tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italians fought back from 1-2 sets down, and trailed 11-17
in the fourth set and again from an 8-11 in the 15-point decider
to tough out a 25-18, 22-25, 30-32, 25-23, 15-12 win.
</P>
<P>
It was their eighth win against two defeats, which brought them
closer to the top three places which carry a berth in the Sydney
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Barcelona Olympic champions Brazil defeated
Cuba 25-23, 25-20, 25-20 to keep their mathematical hopes of
taking an Olympic berth alive.
</P>
<P>
Cuba stood with seven wins against three defeats, while Brazil
and Spain had six wins against four defeats and will have to wait
for the results of other matches to judge their chances of making
Sydney.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Canada edged past Asian champions China 22-25,
25-23, 18-25, 25-23, 15-13 for their fifth win, while Argentina
downed African champions Tunisia 25-10, 25-23, 29-27 for their
third win. 
</P>
