<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Parliament Expects Full Support From China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 1 (Xinhua)-- Indonesia's House of
Representatives (DPR) Wednesday expressed the hope that a positive
result could come out from President Abdurrahman Wahid's three-day
visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of House commission I for security and foreign affairs
Yasril Ananta Baharuddin told Xinhua that Indonesia needs the
Chinese government's support in a bid to overcome (problems) in
the internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that China will give Indonesia full political and
economical support. Therefore we can overcome our internal affairs
soon and lift the country out of the current crisis," Baharuddin
said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian president Wahid left here Wednesday morning for
Beijing to pay a state visit to China at the invitation of Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Baharuddin said that politically China is a very strategic
country in international world.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore we hope that with the president visit (in China) the
two countries will be closer and closer in diplomatic
relationship," he added.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China is a big country that has a veto right
in the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
"With this position (in U.N. Security Council), we must regard
China as an important country, besides, China is our close
neighbor," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also expected that the president could attract China's
investors and urge them to invest in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
"If China's investors start investing (in Indonesia), it will
be very good and it can help our country come out of the economic
crisis soon," he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
