<HEADLINE> Czech Republic, Croatia Join Hands in Fighting Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Czech Interior Minister Vaclav
Grulich and his visiting Croatian counterpart Ivan Penic sighed
here Tuesday two treaties on extradition and anti-crime
cooperation between the police of their countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the treaties, the Czech Republic and Croatia decided to
join hands to fight terrorism, organized crimes, drug trafficking
and illegal arms sales and intensify the drive against criminals.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will timely exchange information and rapidly
detain suspects to recover stolen goods, cars in particular.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Czech Republic has been actively involving
itself in international cooperation on fighting crimes. It has so
far signed treaties on extradition with other 11 countries and on
anti-crime efforts with other 24 countries. 
</P>
