<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Jews Apply for Immigration to Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Many Ethiopian Jews have
applied for immigration at the Israeli embassy in Addis Ababa, the
Reporter newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Some 26,000 Ethiopian Jews are estimated to be residing in
Ethiopia, of which over 8,500 are living in Gondar and the rest
scattered over the northern regions of Ethiopia, the report said.
</P>
<P>
More than 40,000 Ethiopian Jews have immigrated to Israel in
the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 70 percent of Ethiopian Jews settled in Israel still
live in caravans or temporary housing camps while the remaining
are housed in residential buildings, according to Ilan Hartu,
president of the Africa- Israel Friendship Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
