<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 0.29 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks edged up 45.
33 points, or 0.29 percent, to close at 15,422.52 points Wednesday,
lifted by gains in two market heavyweights.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index ended up 45.33 points or 0.29 percent at 15,
422.52, after losing 1.5 percent on Tuesday. Turnover was 10.557
billion Hong Kong dollars (1.35 billion U.S. dollars), down from
Tuesday's 11.07 billion HK dollars (1.419 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Cheung Kong Holdings and its affiliate, Hutchison Whampoa
surged on the news that U.S. mobile equipment maker Motorola is
selling part of its 30 percent stake in Hutchison Telecom to a
buyer.
</P>
<P>
Hutchison Whampoa soared 2.50 Hong Kong dollars to 98.00. while
property giant Cheung Kong gained 3.00 dollars to close at 90.25.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, Utilities, properties and Commerce &AMP;
Industry gained 0.64 percent, 2.15 percent and 0.12 percent
respectively, while Finance lost 0.51 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index went down 1.29 percent and
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index closed down by 0.14
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
