<HEADLINE> Indian Exports Up 21.65 Percent in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- India's export growth jumped
to an impressive 21.65 percent in October 1999 compared to the
same period last year, according to the latest trade data released
by the Commerce Ministry Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The export growth in October was the highest in the current
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Exports recorded a 12.01 percent growth in September and 10.16
percent in August.
</P>
<P>
India's cumulative exports in dollar terms grew by 10.02
percent during April-October compared with the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit for the period was 5.80 billion dollars,
slightly lower than the deficit of 5.82 billion dollars in the
comparable period of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
