<HEADLINE> Russia Takes World Cup Men's Volleyball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 1 (Xinhua) -- European silver medalists Russia
outplayed hosts Japan in three sets to secure the World Cup men's
volleyball tournament title here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A 33-31, 25-20, 25-12 victory gave the Russians their ninth win
of the tournament against one defeat and an unbeatable advantage
on the table.
</P>
<P>
Even if they lose to Spain in three sets on the final day
Thursday and their closest rivals Italy beat Cuba in three sets,
Italy cannot overtake them because of Russia's better set ratio.
</P>
<P>
It was Russia's first victory in the three major events -- the
Olympics, the world championships and World Cup -- since 1991.
</P>
</TEXT>
