<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,506 fishermen are
still missing after the supercyclone hit east India's Orissa state
last month.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from the Orissa state government presented
to the Lok Sabha (lower house of parliament) Wednesday, the
cyclone claimed 9,885 lives and 444,000 livestock also perished.
</P>
<P>
The cyclone affected 12.56 million people and 14,190 villages,
damaging 1.829 million houses and 1.843 million hectares of
cropped area. 
