<HEADLINE> Iranian Minister Calls for Cultural Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Minister of Culture and
Islamic Guidance Ataollah Mohajerani on Wednesday called for
cultural exchanges among Islamic countries in the age of
"globalized" economies and communications.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inaugural session of the fifth Conference of
Islamic Information Ministers held here, Mohajerani expressed hope
that the conference would gain a deeper understanding about
impediments on the way of expanding information and cultural
exchanges among Islamic countries.
</P>
<P>
"Nowadays, information and communication sectors of our
countries face challenges of globalization of economies and
communications," he said, quoted by the Islamic Republic News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
