of information production and dissemination of the Islamic
countries," he said. However, the role which has been playing by
the Islamic states in the global communication does not match the
significance of the Islamic culture and civilization.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the stability, security and development of
Islamic countries would be guaranteed through adoption of balanced
and comprehensive strategies in the fields of information and
knowledge and the related technology.
</P>
<P>
In the age of "globalized" economies and communications, he
said, there is no alternative but employment of modern
communications technology, promotion of cooperation among news
agencies and mass media of the Islamic states, as well as
adoption of measures to portray a more appealing image of Islam
and Muslims.
</P>
<P>
Mohajerani called for a revision and contemplation on the
Islamic information strategy to study its executive methods and
settle financial problems facing the information sector.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the two-day conference would work out
guidelines for further activating the Islamic States Broadcasting
Organization and find a way to increase TV and radio programs
exchange or establish a joint bank of Islamic states' TV
products. 
