<HEADLINE> SADC to Seek Solution to Congolese War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba said on Wednesday the Southern African Development
Community (SADC) will continue making efforts to find a solution
to the conflict in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
Citing the Middle East peace process as an example, he said
that it is not easy to find the final solution, but the DRC peace
process is on track.
</P>
<P>
He told a press briefing at State House that the meeting of the
Joint Military Commission (JMC) is going well in Harare, Zimbabwe,
while sometime it will come to Lusaka, Zambia.
</P>
<P>
JMC was set up to monitor the ceasefire agreement signed in
July and August by countries involved in the conflict and the
rebels. 
</P>
