<HEADLINE> Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and visiting Indonesian President
Abdurrahman Wahid agreed in their talks this afternoon to develop
a long-term, stable, good-neighborly and trusting relationship
that covers all forms of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The fact that President Wahid chose China as the destination of
his first state visit since he assumed office demonstrates that he
attaches great importance to developing relations with China,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"We are highly appreciative of the fact," the Chinese president
added.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese President Meets U.S. Senator
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin met with U.S. Senator Larry Craig
and his delegation this afternoon at the Great Hall of the People
here.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that both China and the United States are determined
to bring the sound, stable and growing Sino-U.S. relations into
the new century. "This is not only in the interests of the peoples
in our two countries, but also conductive to peace and development
of the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Taking the recently signed Sino-U.S. agreement on China's
admission into the World Trade Organization (WTO) as an example,
Jiang pointed out that both China and the U.S. should review major
issues that are of fundamental interest to Sino-U.S. relations and
the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice-President Meets Iranian Vice-President
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao met with his Iranian
counterpart Mohammad Hashemi who is in Beijing to attend the tenth
session of the China-Iran Joint Committee on Economic, Trade,
Scientific and Technological Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that both China and Iran have long and great
civilizations and have maintained a steady development in
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to Iran's status and role in
regional and international affairs, and would like to continue
friendly relations with Iran on the basis of the Five Principles
of Peaceful Coexistence, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Meets Greek Guest
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian said here today that China
values its relationship with Greece and he hopes that the two
countries will further promote bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
state councilor, made the remarks while meeting with Vice Admiral
Christos Kazassis, Deputy Chief of Hellenic National Defence
General Staff.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that in recent years, China and Greece have witnessed
sustained development, and exchanges between their respective
armed forces have helped improve mutual understanding, trust and
friendship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
