<HEADLINE> Palestinian, Israeli Ministers Visit EU Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Justice Minister
Freih Abu Medein and Israeli Justice Minister Yossi Beilin visited
the European Commission, the European Union's executive branch, on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that Israelis and Palestinians hold a
joint visit at ministerial level to the European Union executives'
headquarters, EU officials said.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission said in a written statement that this "
unprecedented event" of the two-day joint visit confirms the
growing momentum of Israeli-Palestinian relations in the past
months as well as the continued involvement of the European Union
in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers will hold joint and bilateral meetings with
EU Commissioner Antonio Vitorino, who is in charge of the Justice
and Home Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The three parties will explore possibilities for the planned
Legal Liaison Office (LLO).
</P>
<P>
"The LLO will bring Israeli and Palestinian jurists together to
help create and regulate the infrastructure for joint legal
cooperation, to propose legislation for facilitation for economic
and trade relations and to assist cooperation in special cases
such as child custody and labor issues," the Commission said.
</P>
</TEXT>
