<HEADLINE> Macao 14k Triad Member Detained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Wong Tat-hou, a key member of
the 14k triad branch in Macao, was arrested recently in southwest
China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The news was announced at a press briefing held by the Public
Security Department in Zhuhai today.
</P>
<P>
Wong was sentenced in absentia in the first ruling held on
November 23. And the court of Macao asked the public security
departments in inland areas of China to assist in capturing Wong.
</P>
<P>
In response to the appeal, the Public Security Department of
Guangdong province formed a special task force and coordinated
efforts with police in Zhuhai, Zhongshan and Guangzhou cities.
</P>
<P>
After a thorough investigation, they tracked Wong down in
Yunnan and detained him there.
</P>
<P>
Wong has been turned over to Macao police. 
