<HEADLINE> Russia Protests to U.S. at Spy Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Wednesday lodged an
official protest against the U.S. over an espionage incident by a
staff member of the U.S. Embassy in Moscow, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A representative of the U.S. Embassy was called to the Russian
Foreign Ministry where he was handed a note of protest, Interfax
said, quoting a source with the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. diplomat, identified as 33-year-old Cheri Leberknight,
was caught on the spot while receiving classified military-
strategic materials from a Russian citizen on Monday, FSB
spokesman Alexander Zdanovich said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Interfax said the Russian Foreign Ministry has demanded
Leberknight, a second secretary of the military political section
of the U.S. Embassy, leave Russia.
</P>
<P>
The incident came at a time when Russian-U.S. relations were
at the lowest since the end of the Cold War, but Russian Foreign
Minister Igor Ivanov expressed the hope Tuesday that it "will not
impact on the development of bilateral relations." 
</P>
</TEXT>
