<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Acrobatic Performance Staged for Int'l Ozone Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 1,000 participants at an
international meeting on ozone layer protection were treated to an
evening of entertainment tonight after three busy days, thanks to
the performance of acrobatics hosted by the Beijing Municipal
People's Government.
</P>
<P>
The performance was staged by Chinese Acrobatic Troupe at China
Grand Theater in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, known as the 11th Meeting of the Parties to the
Montreal Protocol on Substances that Deplete Ozone Layer, is an
annual event to discuss the implementation of international
programs designed to control the production and consumption of
ozone-damaging chemicals.
</P>
<P>
About 180 countries, regions and organizations are represented
at the five-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
Liu Qi, mayor of Beijing, met with Shafqat Kakakhel, deputy
executive director of the United Nations Environment Program, and
some of the participants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
