<HEADLINE> State Council Circular on Production Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The State Council issued an
urgent circular today asking all localities in China to do a good
job of production safety.
</P>
<P>
The circular called on all departments and areas to adhere to
the principle of "safety and prevention first" and keep an eye on
weak links in production in order to curb major accidents.
</P>
<P>
All localities and departments should stress the safety of such
key installations as airports, railway stations, oil warehouses
and department stores, the circular said.
</P>
<P>
A comprehensive check on production safety will be carried out
in the country immediately. Priority will be given to airports,
railway stations, highways, coal mines, petrol-chemical works,
fireworks factories and key projects.
</P>
<P>
Those who are directly responsible for the accidents and
leading officials who neglect their duty will be punished in
accordance with the law, the circular said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
