<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1400 GMT, December 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEATTLE -- The third ministerial meeting of the World Trade
Organization (WTO) started here Tuesday after a few hours of delay
caused by protesters who block every intersection to the venue of
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
An opening ceremony was canceled and the meeting went directly
into a plenary negotiating session. Director-General Mike Moore of
WTO officially announced the opening of the meeting at the session.
(TWO-Seattle)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Zambian President Frederick Chiluba said on Wednesday
the Southern African Development Community (SADC) will continue
making efforts to find a solution to the conflict in the
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
Citing the Middle East peace process as an example, he said
that it is not easy to find the final solution, but the DRC peace
process is on track. (Zambia-Congo-Solution)
</P>
