<HEADLINE> Hong Kong, Japan Business Cooperation Committees Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong-Japan and Japan-
Hong Kong Business Cooperation Committees met here Wednesday to
promote trade, investment, tourism and understanding between the
two economies.
</P>
<P>
The meeting agreed that Hong Kong's role as an intermediary and
regional services hub will become increasingly important for
Japanese companies, enabling them to approach the Chinese inland
market by taking advantage of Hong Kong's established legal,
administrative and managerial capacities.
</P>
<P>
The committees agreed to convene their next joint plenary
session at a time convenient for both sides in Japan in 2000.
</P>
<P>
Total trade between Japan and Hong Kong exceeded 32 billion U.S.
dollars last year, and Japan is Hong Kong's third largest export
market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
