<HEADLINE> Security Council Has New President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Jeremy Greenstock, the
British permanent representative to the United Nations, Wednesday
succeeds Danilo Turk of Slovenia as President of the U.N. Security
Council.
</P>
<P>
The Council presidency rotates alphabetically every month among
its 15 members.
</P>
<P>
The Iraq and Congo (K) problems are expected to be high on the
agenda of the Security Council, which, under the U.N. Charter, has
the primary responsibility for the maintenance of peace and
security in the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
