<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Regrets Raid on Turkish News Agency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 1 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for Pakistan's
Information Ministry expressed his "deep regret" over the raid by
some unidentified persons on the office of a Turkish news agency
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman assured the Turkish News Agency that strict
action would be taken against the culprits and that no such
incident would take place in future.
</P>
<P>
No such incident could ever have an adverse effect on the close
and brotherly relations between the peoples and the governments of
Pakistan and Turkey, he added.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said five people who identified themselves as
officers of the Intelligence Bureau raided the office of Turkish
Zaman International Agency and kept the entire staff under
detention.
</P>
<P>
Zaman's bureau chief Halit Esendir said the five people kept
the entire staff under detention and even did not allow them to
use any telephone.
</P>
<P>
They were apparently unarmed, but threatened to abduct if the
staff members did not cooperate, Esendir said.
</P>
<P>
It is still unknown what is the motive for the raid incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
